insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1223', 'encode', '[ɪnkod]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=encode', '{vt.}++把(电文、消息、情报等)译成密码或电码：**++【计算机】把…编码：**', '++The only solution is to encode data to a safe set of characters.**++惟一可行的解决方案是将数据编码为一组安全的字符。**++Usually, their processors encode information into either individual atoms or molecules made up of two atoms.**++通常，处理器通过单个原子或由两个原子组成的分子进行信息编码。**++These changes basically take a section of the description and encode it into RDF serialization.**++这些更改基本上是抽取描述的一部分并将其编码为 RDF 序列化。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1224', 'formulate', '[fɔrmjəlet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=formulate', '{vt.}++使公式化；用公式表示；把…化成公式**++系统(或确切)地阐述(或提出)(理论、计划等)：**++构想出(计划、方法等)；规划(制度等)**++制定…的配方；按配方制造(或配制)**', '++You observe the software-related phenomena and start to formulate an hypothesis.**++您观察与软件相关的现象并开始明确表达出一个假设。**++If a question asks you to take a position on some issue, try to formulate a more nuanced answer.**++如果一个问题问你在某些问题中采取什么立场，那么尝试制订更细致的回答。**++Our American partners, unlike what was happening in recent years have taken a pause and now they will formulate and take a final position.**++我们的美国伙伴，与过去几年的做法有所不同的是，他们已经暂停下来。 现在他们将重新规划，并确定最后的立场。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1225', 'obsession', '[əbsɛʃ(ə)n]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=obsession', '{n.}++着迷；困扰**++被迷住(或困扰、烦扰)的状态**++烦扰人的情绪(或思想、冲动等)**++着魔**++【心理学】强迫观念，强迫症**', '++Nonetheless, foreign women—like the nurses—appear to have been something of an obsession.**++然而，外国妇女似乎也会有几分困扰，比如说前面提到的护士。**++"We have an obsession today with fat and cholesterol because we can go to the market and stuff ourselves with it," Stanford said.**++对此，斯坦福表示：“今天，我们被脂肪和胆固醇困扰是因为我们能随时去超市用这些食品将自己填饱。**++Plagiarism is like that; it’s an insider’s obsession.**++剽窃也是如此：它只是内部人员的困扰。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1226', 'legion', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=legion', '{n.}++【罗马历史】古罗马军团(通常由约3 000至6 000名步兵组，并辅以骑兵)**++众多的士兵；大批的部队；大军；军团**++大量；大批；众多**++[常作 L-](半)军事性单位、协会(或团体)**++[L-] American Legion, Foreign Legion 的缩略形式**{adj.}++大量的；大批的；众多的**', '++Outside the church door, veterans from the British Legion form a guard of honor.**++在教堂大门外，有来自英国军团的退伍老兵组成的仪仗队。**++She asked her legion of fans -- whom she calls "Little Monsters" -- to buy a bracelet on her website saying, "We Pray for Japan," for donations of $5 or more.**++她号召被她称作小恶人的众多的粉丝,都参与到她的网站来，“捐出5美金甚至更多的善款的同时让我们为日本祈福“。**++It keeps you in touch with the people you already know. It lets them know you haven’t died or joined the French Foreign Legion.**++这让你和你早已认识的人保持联系，让他们知道你还活着或是没有加入法国外籍军团。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1227', 'engender', '[ɪndʒɛndɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=engender', '{vt.}++产生，造成，酿成；招致，引起；使出现，使发生：**++[罕用语]生(子女)，生育，生殖**{vi.}++被造成；发生，产生，生成，(逐渐)形成；开始存在：**++被造成；发生，产生，生成，(逐渐)形成；开始存在：**', '++In such circumstances, governments must do all they can to create and engender trust among its nation’s constituents and institutions.**++在这种情况下，政府必须尽其所能在它的国家选民和公共机构之间创造和产生信任。**++Retrospectives on the process and working practices regularly capture the lessons learned by the project and engender a culture of continuous process improvement within the project.**++对过程和工作实践的回顾有规律地捕捉从项目中得到的经验，并在项目中造成一个持续的过程改进的文化。**++In addition to showing some of the ways that computers can find their way invisibly into people@s lives, this speculation points up some of the social issues that embodied virtuality will engender.**++除了显示出计算机如何找到无形进入人们生活的方式的一些方法外，这种猜测指出了一些嵌入式虚拟可能产生的社会问题。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1228', 'predispose', '[pridɪspoz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=predispose', '{vt.}++预先处理；使倾向于；使易接受：**++使预先有倾向；使预先有意向：**{vi.}++引起易感性 (to):**++引起易感性 (to):**', '++If the mutations discovered in the tissue cells actually predispose for AAA, they present an ideal target for new therapies, and may have even wider therapeutic implications.**++如果在组织细胞中发现的突变实际上更易导致AAA，那么就为他们提出了一个新疗法的理想目标，并且还可能扩展治疗学。**++What is more, failure to consider the perspectives of such partners will potentially predispose them to work with other vendors with whom they will have better opportunities for collaboration.**++更重要的是，他们通常会忽略考虑这类合伙人的观点，从而会偏向于使这些人与其他可能会与他们有更多合作机会的人进行合作。**++"Engaging in one type of environmentally friendly behavior can predispose one to engage in similar behaviors, inhibit other behaviors, or even increase environmentally harmful behaviors, " said Swim.**++斯维姆说，“从事一类对环境有益的事能使一人偏向做相似的行为，抑制别样行为，或者甚至能增加对环境有害的行为。”**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1229', 'subtlety', '[sʌtlti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=subtlety', '{n.}++稀薄，清淡**++隐约，模糊**++纤细**++纤巧；微妙；敏感，巧妙；难以捉摸**++微妙的地方**++微妙(或难以捉摸)的东西**++精妙，精细；细微的区别**++精妙之处；细微之处**++细心；敏锐**++诡秘，狡猾；诡计**', '++You encounter one subtlety, though: How do you order the digits?**++不过有一个微妙之处：如何排列数字？**++Indeed this subtlety is precisely why run-time exceptions are a bad idea for external conditions that should be handled by code.**++正是由于这个微妙的原因，让运行时异常成为代码要处理的外部状况是一个坏主意。**++A few hours after Singh@s Yankee plainspokenness, Obama delivered a speech to India@s Parliament with a subtlety and political skill worthy of the nation@s great statesmen.**++辛格的美式直率几小时后，奥巴马在印度议会发表了一个配得上这个国家伟大政治家敏锐和富于政治技巧的讲话。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1230', 'imitator', '[ɪmɪtetɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=imitator', '{n.}', '++If you don@t know where your ideas are coming from, you@re probably imitating an imitator.**++如果你不知道你的想法从哪里来,你可能在模仿一个模仿者.**++On Saturday, they giggled at a Michael Jackson imitator wearing headphones and doing a comically poor imitation of the artist, seemingly for himself.**++一位迈克杰克逊的模仿者逗得他们咯咯笑，他戴着耳机，滑稽地模仿麦克，好像并不为给别人看。**++Suffice it to say, you won@t find many original ideas here, and when a successful idea comes from either company, an imitator just as quickly appears from the other.**++无须多说，你在这里找不到很多独创的创意，当一个公司得到了一个成功的创意，模仿者很快就会出现在其它公司。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1231', 'continuator', '[kəntɪnjʊ,etɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=continuator', '{n.}', '++If a affective legacy is wonderful enough to continuator, he would have a everlasting spring. Then we should show our sensation.**++然而，如果一份情感的遗产，足以让继承它的人恒久地享有春天，那么，我们不更应该奉上自己的感动吗？**++Whether you are the anti-innovator or the traditional continuator, the indispensable premise and foundation is fully understanding about tradition.**++无论是反传统的革新者，还是维护传统的继承派，都必须充分地认识并理解传统是其必要的前提和基础。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1232', 'successor', '[səksɛsɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=successor', '{n.}++后继者，继承者**++接任者，继任者，接替者**++后继的事物**', '++Son and successor of David.**++大卫的儿子和继承者。**++What message would you prepare for your successor?**++你会为你的继任者准备什么样的信函？**++Once there was an emperor in the Far East who was growing old and knew it was coming time to choose his successor.**++从前在遥远的东方，有一位皇帝，随着岁月的流逝，年事已高的他意识到该是找一个继任者的时候了。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1233', 'caliber', '[kæləbɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=caliber', '{n.}', '++Perhaps the first thing that students notice about their college is the caliber of their fellow students.**++可能学生们对这所大学关注的第一件事就是同学的才干。**++The ringers (i.e., nonscientists) at last week’s hearing weren’t of quite the same caliber, but their prepared testimony still had some memorable moments.**++这些伪专家（非科学家）上周的口径并不完全一致，但是他们事先准备好的证词有着似曾相识的感觉。**++One of the criminals immediately shoved a .38 caliber handgun to my head, ordered me to the cooler, pushed me down on the floor, and pumped a bullet into the back of my head - execution style.**++其中一个匪徒迅速掏出一把口径为38毫米的手枪用力指着我的头，勒令我走到冷冻机旁，然后把我推倒在地，像执行死刑般从后面朝我头部开了一枪。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1234', 'peculiarly', '[pɪkjʊljɚli]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=peculiarly', '{adv.}{adj.}++特有的；独具的；(个人或团体)独有的**++特别的；特殊的；奇特的**++罕见的；奇怪的；怪僻的**++个人的；(财产等)私人的**++[口语]有点不舒服的**{n.}++特有财产；特权**++(不受当地司法机关管辖的)特殊教会(或教区)**++[P-]【基督教】上帝的特选子民(指基督徒)；犹太人**++[P-]信仰疗法怪人团(peculiar people) 成员**++【印刷】(常用成套活字外的)特殊活字**', '++There are no peculiarly Western or Eastern mobile phones or financial derivatives.**++没有特别专属于西方或东方的移动电话或金融衍生品。**++It is not true that my peculiarly isolated social condition was the bar to my plunging into the midst of the world-life.**++假如说，我那特别孤立的社会环境阻止了我进入人世生活的中心，这是不正确的。**++But the way its themes dovetail with Gibson@s disgrace make it — peculiarly enough — the right film for him to have made in this very wrong moment.**++但是电影的主题和吉布森的耻辱完全吻合，特别奇怪的使它成为在这个错误时间里对他最合适的电影。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1235', 'gravitas', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=gravitas', '{n.}', '++The second: when you do come down strongly on someone’s side, refer to a higher authority to give yourself the requisite gravitas.**++第二守则，如果你很确定地站在某人一边，要搬出一个更高的权威，给你那必需的庄严。**++The Presidents gave bipartisan gravitas to the campaign, and we needed all the help we could get.**++总统们到场为这个活动带来了两党合作的庄严气氛，而我们需要所有能够得到的帮助。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1236', 'receptiveness', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=receptiveness', '{n.}{adj.}++接受的；接纳的；容纳的**++(建议等)易接受的**++(对新思想、新知识等)善于接受的；接受能力强的**++感官的；感受器的**', '++A state of intensified attention and receptiveness , and an increased responsiveness to an idea or to a set of ideas.**++一种加强了集中力以及接受能力的状态，对于一个意见或一套意见增强了反应能力。**++Group intelligence is correlated, Malone and his colleagues found, with the average social sensitivity — the openness, and receptiveness, to others — of a group@s constituents.**++马龙和他的同事们发现团队智能是和团队成员的平均社会敏感度——开放性，接受能力等等相关联的。**++In the days of their youth it was natural, but the receptiveness of youth has departed, and they cannot see.**++他们在青年的日子，这是自然的，但是青年的感受性一经离开，他们就都看不见了。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1237', 'chariot', '[tʃærɪət]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=chariot', '{n.}++古代双轮马拉战车**++[古语] 轻便四轮马车 (供游览或隆重场合用)**++[诗歌用语] 庄严华丽的彩车**++[俚语] 老式汽车，老爷车**{vt.}++用战车 (或马车) 运送**{vi.}++驾驭战车 (或马车)**', '++O mother， the young Prince did pass by our door， and the morning sun flashed from his chariot.**++呵，母亲，年轻的王子已经从我们门前走过了，从他的车辇里射出朝日的金光。**++So, he did the worst possible thing he could: postpone the next chariot race.**++所以他作出了一个最坏的决定：推迟下一场拉战车比赛。**++When humans first started building things, determining whether they would work as planned was mostly a matter of trial and error. Build a bridge, drive a chariot across it, and see if it collapsed.**++一开始人类建造房屋时,决定房屋是否合格的方法是去试一下,看看有什么不妥的地方.建成一座桥,把辆战车开上面跑一跑,看看桥会不会倒.**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1238', 'cavalry', '[kævlri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=cavalry', '{n.}++[总称]骑兵**++【军事】高度机动的地面部队 (原指骑兵部队，现常指摩托化部队、机械化部队、装甲部队)**', '++The cavalry coursed the fleeing troops.**++骑兵追赶逃跑的败兵。**++We were taken in flank by a troop of cavalry.**++我们翼侧受到一队骑兵的袭击。**++The cavalry unit must be remounted immediately.**++骑兵部队必须立即补充新马。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1239', 'diffusion', '[dɪfjʊʒən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=diffusion', '{n.}++扩散，散开；散播；弥漫**++【人类学、社会学】**++(一种文化的要素特点向另一种文化的)传播，(文化、知识、消息等的)传播，散布，普及**++(社会习俗、神话、技能等跨越文化群落的)传流，传播**', '++The invention of printing helped the diffusion of learning.**++印刷术的发明有助于知识的传播。**++To understand that you have core power distribution that you can calculate using diffusion theory but that core power distribution creates a flux.**++理解你的核心动力分布,你能计算使用扩散理论,但是核心动力分布创造了一个流量。**++And that is why this fixed law of diffusion applies.**++这就是这个混合的扩散理论运用的原因。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1240', 'metallurgy', '[mɛtəlɝdʒi]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=metallurgy', '{n.}', '++With your knowledge of metallurgy, you can turn the wreckage of your spaceship into tools and weapons.**++用你的冶金知识，可以把飞船的残骸转化成工具和武器；**++You might say, well what@s the person who studied chemical metallurgy doing teaching chemistry here? Well, after my Ph.D., MIT I came here as a postdoctoral fellow in 1977.**++你们可能会问，这个学习,化学冶金学的人怎么会在这教,化学呢，好吧，在我拿到博士学位后，1977年我作为一名博士后来到了。**++Without innumerable advances in immunology, biochemistry, chemical engineering, statistics and metallurgy, to name but a few, I wouldn@t be where I am now – in fact I wouldn@t be at all.**++如果没有免疫学、生物化学、化学工程、统计学和冶金学等等领域无数的进步，我不会是现在这样，事实上我可能根本不存在了。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1241', 'desiccation', '[,dɛsɪkeʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=desiccation', '{n.}{vt.}++把…弄干，使干(燥)，使完全干燥；使脱水：**++用干燥法保存(食物)，干贮(食物)；晒干；烘干；烤干：**++使智力枯竭；使…的感情枯竭**{vi.}++变成完全干燥，变干；变枯竭：**++变成完全干燥，变干；变枯竭：**{adj.}++枯燥无味的；毫无生气的；无精打采的**', '++The fungi don@t survive the desiccation, so the longer the bdelloids stay dry, the better off they be.**++真菌不能在干燥的地方存活，因此蛭形轮虫保持干燥的时间越长，它们状况会更好。**++The fungi don’t survive the desiccation, so the longer the bdelloids stay dry, the better off they be.**++真菌无法在干燥中存活，因此蛭形轮虫保持干燥的时间越长，他们就会脱离真菌越好。**++We travelled north to Tillaberi, a rolling landscape of sand, wind-blown dust, and sparsely scattered bushes and trees, seemingly in the very last stages of desiccation.**++我们一直向北到了提拉贝里，那里是一片荒凉—飞沙，飞尘还有稀疏的树木，看起来也即将要干枯了。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1242', 'demographic', '[,dɛməɡræfɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=demographic', '{adj.}++人口的**++人口学的**++人口统计的**', '++As we described earlier, personas represent user groups; in an artifact, they can be supported with demographic and other data.**++如我们早先描述的，角色代表用户组，在工件中，他们可以由人口统计和其他数据支持。**++Yet it has barely begun to face up to the demographic challenge, even though that is likely to exacerbate those inequalities among the young as well as the old.**++然而，民主党还没怎么开始正视人口结构带来的挑战，即使这样可能会加重那些年轻人还有老年人中间的不平等现象。**++But will India be able to transform its demographic transition into long-term sustainable economic growth?**++但是，印度能否将人口构成的变化，转化为经济的长期可持续增长？**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1243', 'shrine', '[ʃraɪn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=shrine', '{n.}++神龛；圣坛**++圣殿，神祠，圣祠**++神庙**++圣地，神圣的场所；神圣之物**++神圣物品箱；圣骨匣；圣陵**++[S-](美国)圣地兄弟会**{vt.}++[诗歌用语]= enshrine**', '++The infidels defiled the holy shrine.**++异教徒亵渎神圣的神殿。**++You can even make a shrine or an altar that you can face when you sit in meditation.**++你甚至可以制作一个神龛或者祭坛，这样当你冥想的时候就可以面对它们而坐。**++Inside, the prayer hall stretched along the length of the courtyard; in the centre people posed for pictures beside the shrine of John the Baptist.**++里面的祈祷大厅就和庭院一般长度，大厅中央，人们摆姿势在约翰施洗先知的神龛边上拍照留念。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1244', 'coerce', '[koɝs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=coerce', '{vt.}++强制，胁迫；迫使：**++支配，抑制，压制**', '++And if the attacker should coerce the program into executing another file, all capabilities will be dropped and the file will be executed as an unprivileged user.**++另外，如果攻击者迫使这个程序执行另一个文件，那么所有能力都会撤消，将作为非特权用户执行这个文件。**++The real magic in MochiKit.DOM is its willingness to flexibly coerce various types of objects into the right types during method calls, including doing so recursively.**++DOM 真正的魔法在于它在方法调用过程中积极而灵活地把各种对象类型强制转换成正确的类型，包括在递归过程中。**++They warn that sooner or later the ECB will be forced to take further measures to coerce banks to start lending.**++他们告诫称,欧央行迟早会被迫出台进一步措施,强制银行开始往外放贷.**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1245', 'demise', '[dɪmaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=demise', '{n.}++死亡**++(行动或存在的)终止，终结；失败；地位(或职位)的丧失**++【政府】(如因死亡或退位)让位，转位，传位，禅位**++【法律】**++(引起财产遗赠的)死亡**++(财产的)转让，让与，移交；遗赠**{vt.}++【政府】(如因死亡或退位)传(位)，让(位)，逊(位)，传(王位、君权等)，禅让(王位、君权等)**++【法律】(在有限时间内)转让(地位等)；遗赠(产业)**++[废语]传达；传送**{vi.}++死，去世**++【法律】转让；遗赠**', '++Unfortunately, in our society, after age 25 or so, many folks begin to focus on any glitch in memory as evidence for its demise.**++不幸的是,在我们的社会,在25岁左右或者更大些,许多人开始关注在记忆方面的任何故障作为其死亡的证据。**++I sought not only my own salvation, but also to account for the bizarre demise of the clerk, who must no doubt have been discovered on the street below.**++这样做不仅是为了挽救自己，也是为了解释那位管理员古怪的死亡，现在人们无疑已经发现街上他的尸体了。**++Indeed, al Qaeda has slaughtered scores of Muslims in many countries, including our own. So his demise should be welcomed by all who believe in peace and human dignity.**++确实，基地组织在包括我们国家在内的很多国家屠杀了大量穆斯林，所以，他的死亡应该受到所有相信世界和平和人类尊严的人们的欢迎。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1246', 'livable', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=livable', '{adj.}++(房子、气候等)适于居住的；舒适的**++(生活)过得去的；有生活价值的；能忍受的；能持久的**++(人)易于相处的；可与之共同生活的(常与with连用)[亦作 liveable]**', '++In many neighborhoods, someone forgot to plan for that basic building block of livable cities, the sidewalk.**++在许多社区，有人竟然忘记为这些适宜居住的城市修建基础设施——人行道。**++However, today, the Government of China fully recognizes that preserving the country’s heritage is an essential part of creating livable, sustainable cities.**++然而，现在中国政府已充分认识到，保护国家的遗产是建设适于居住、可持续发展的城市的一项重要内容。**++Addressing the twin challenges of climate change and energy security will also help make the region’s rapidly growing cities more livable.**++应对气候变化和能源安全的双重挑战，也有助于使该地区快速扩张的城市更适宜居住。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1247', 'episode', '[ɛpɪsod]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=episode', '{n.}++(组成一个较大事件的)一个(或一系列)事件，(若干或一连串事件中的)一个事件 **++(人生的)一段经历**', '++I ask what the episode taught him.**++我问这段插曲给了他什么教训。**++A year ago, my average week was something like a Sex and The City episode.**++一年前，我每周的生活就是性和城市小插曲之类的东西。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1248', 'outflow', '[aʊtflo]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=outflow', '{n.}++流出**++流出量**++流出物**{vi.}++流出**', '++In contrast, nothing lives in the Dead Sea because, with no outflow, the lake has stagnated.**++相反，死海里没有生命，因为没有水流出去，这个湖是停滞不动的。**++We’re not supposed to retain a drop, and [even] during a stated period of construction, inflow is equal to outflow.**++他说“我们不应该截流哪怕一滴水，即使在规定的施工期间，流进的水量和流出的水量也是相等的。”**++The outflow of funds from Britain puts the spotlight on hedge fund threats to abandon the UK because of higher taxes, tighter regulation and potential caps on executive pay and bonuses.**++资金从英国流出将对冲基金因更高的税收、更严格的监管和可能封顶的主管薪酬和奖金而放弃英国的危险放在了聚光灯下。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1249', 'interconnect', '[,ɪntɚkənɛkt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=interconnect', '{vt.}++使互相连接；使互相联系**{adj.}++[美国英语]私人电话与公用电话网连接起来的，互联的，直达连接的**', '++All hosts in the instance must use the same type of interconnect.**++实例中的所有主机必须使用相同类型的互连。**++I@ll explain what happens in each phase and how the phases interconnect, then use an example application to demonstrate the lifecycle in action.**++我们将介绍在每个阶段中会发生什么，以及这些阶段是如何相互连接在一起的，然后使用一个示例程序来展示实际的生命周期。**++To build a sustainable future for people on Earth, she said, we must first understand how our climate, health, economy and social structures all interconnect.**++她说，要为地球上的人建设一个可持续的未来，我们必须先了解我们的气候、健康、经济和社会结构是如何互相关联的。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1250', 'conceivably', '[kənsivəbli]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conceivably', '{adv.}{adj.}', '++But conceivably, this scheme could facilitate a fairly simple and straightforward approach to multithreading: A page could have multiple scripts, and the VM could run them in parallel...**++但是可以想象，这个方案将会使多线程处理变得异常简单和直接：一个页面可以有多个脚本，而且虚拟机可以并行运行它们……**++Conceivably, some of them might reduce the badness of death, in some way.**++可以想到，某些特征可能会降低其坏处，在某种程度上。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1251', 'detractor', '[dɪtræktɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=detractor', '{n.}', '++John Locke is both a supporter and detractor from the theory of Libertarianism.**++洛克（John Locke）既是自由意志论的支持者，也是它的批评者。**++But for every fan there is a detractor, critical not just of the monastery@s approach but Shi@s own lifestyle.**++有一个粉丝，就会有一个批评者。 人们不仅批评少林寺的经营方式，还批评释本人的生活方式。**++The attack took many by surprise, because few had anticipated that the major detractor of the faith would be one of our own.**++这一攻击使许多人非常惊奇，因为很少人料想到信仰的主要诽谤者竟是我们自己中间的一位。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1252', 'proponent', '[prəponənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=proponent', '{n.}++提议者；建议者；动议者**++支持者；辩护者**++【法律】提出认证遗嘱者**{adj.}++建议的；提议的**++支持的；辩护的**', '++He was an early proponent of the theory that life on Earth may have come from Mars in rocks ejected by asteroid and comet impacts.**++他是这项理论早期的支持者：地球生命也许来自火星，通过小行星和彗星冲撞而由岩石喷射而出。**++Well, ironically, he@s a proponent of giving away content for free as a business model – and for years he@s been telling the music industry to adapt to it.**++嗯，具有讽刺意味的是，他将一个支持者免费赠送东西作为一个商业模型—多年来他讲的音乐产业适合这样发展。**++The US space agency has been working on a project with The Planetary Society, a long-time proponent of the technology.**++美国国家航天局正在计划与太阳帆技术的长期支持者“行星学会”一道开发一套类似的系统。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1253', 'refuge', '[rɛfjʊdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=refuge', '{n.}++避难；庇护**++避难所；收容所**++隐蔽处；安全地带；(马路中间的)安全岛**++权宜之计；慰藉物**{vt.}++[古语]给以庇护；提供庇护**{vi.}++[古语]避难；寻求庇护**', '++If it believed in its own essence, would it … seek refuge in hypocrisy and sophism?**++如果它相信它自己的本质的话，那么它会……在虚伪和诡辩中寻求庇护么？**++He told them that in our area, we are known as a refuge; we treat all victims of the conflict equally, no matter what side they’re on.**++他告诉他们，我们这个地区的人都知道这里是一个避难所；我们对所有的冲突的受害者一视同仁，不论他们属于哪一方。**++Ye have shamed the counsel of the poor, because the LORD is his refuge.**++你们叫困苦人的谋算，变为羞辱。 然而耶和华是他的避难所。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1254', 'sizable', '[saɪzəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sizable', '{adj.}++极大的，相当大的**++[古语]大小合适的，大小方便的[亦作sizeable]**', '++Solar would make a sizable contribution only after 2025, once the expansion of wind energy had plateaued.**++一旦风能的利用趋于稳定，太阳能在将在2025年后做出相当大的贡献.**++But with much of it incurred with little regard for how it would be repaid, a sizable chunk is expected to turn sour.**++但由于几乎无人关心如何偿还这其中的很多债务，所以预计会有相当大一块债务变成坏账。**++It is the first state primary with a sizable African-American population -- about half of Democratic voters will be black.**++这是第一个具有相当数量的非洲裔人口的州的初选──民主党选民中约有一半为黑人。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1255', 'inhospitable', '[,ɪnhɑspɪtəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=inhospitable', '{adj.}++不好客的，招待不热情的；冷淡的；不友好的**++(土地等)贫瘠的，不毛的；荒凉的**++(气候等)险恶的，恶劣的；不适合居住的**++相矛盾的，不相容的；格格不入的(常与to连用)**', '++Serious illness doesn@t bother me for long because I am too inhospitable a host.**++严重的疾病都不会打扰我太久，因为我是个很不好客的主人。**++In the Arctic, above the ice and below, wildlife prospers in what might seem to be an inhospitable environment.**++在北极圈，在冰层上下，野生动植物在一个看起来无法居住的环境中繁荣昌盛。**++Without this mechanism our "Blue Planet" might well be as dry and inhospitable as Mars.**++如果没有这个机制，我们的“蓝色星球”，可能就会象火星一样干旱和不适合居住。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1256', 'impetus', '[ɪmpɪtəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=impetus', '{n.}++促进，推动；激动；刺激；推动力**++【物理学】动量，动力**', '++Children need an impetus to study.**++儿童学习需要动力。**++And so that really was a major impetus, plus my wife always telling me that I should tell this story.**++所以，这确实是一个主要的动力，另外我的妻子总是告诉我应该把这个故事公诸于众。**++They have also provided most of the impetus for the adoption of these practices.**++同时，它们也为这些实践方法的采用提供了很大推动力。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1257', 'paucity', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paucity', '{n.}++少量，少许**++缺乏，贫乏；不足**', '++Overall, the researchers say they were dismayed with the paucity and weakness of the existing evidence.**++最后，研究者们提到他们为现有证据的缺乏和薄弱而感到沮丧。**++But, in the event, they showed a clear recognition that the paucity of black managers has become an embarrassing anomaly that needs radical attention.**++但在调查中，他们明确认可了这一事实：黑人教练的缺乏已成为需要从根本上注意的令人尴尬的异常情况。**++Grappling with these and other questions have been hindered by a paucity of data.**++这些及其他问题的解决都因为缺乏数据而收到阻碍。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1258', 'practitioner', '[præktɪʃənɚ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=practitioner', '{n.}++(尤指医生、律师等)开业者；从业者**++[美国英语]基督教科学派医治者**++从事者；实践者；实习者；练习者**++[古语]策划阴谋者，策士**', '++You can do this by selecting only roles that interest you, as a practitioner.**++作为一名从业者，您可以通过只选择那些您感兴趣的角色来进行操作。**++The only itemthat is constant in all of those is the transformed practitioner.**++在所有这些变化中唯一不变的就是转化的从业者。**++Your doctor, health care practitioner or psychotherapist will help you determine the best course of action to have you feel strong and well again.**++你的医生，健康护理从业者或精神治疗师将帮助你确定最好的治疗方案，去帮助你再次感觉到强壮和健康。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1259', 'technician', '[tɛknɪʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=technician', '{n.}++技术员，技师；技术专家**++(音乐、绘画等艺术方面)技巧熟练者**++(美国)陆军技术军士;陆军上士(现为 sergeant first class)**', '++“Can you blow that up?” she asks the technician.**++“你能把这张放大吗？” 她问那个技术员。**++He has distilled many wonderful stories from his experiences as a crime lab technician.**++他从他作为犯罪实验室技术员的经验中，写出许多精彩的故事。**++Wiley Reed, 31, an aircraft components technician, said: @We are a very close family, and I think it is that that is helping us through this as well.**++31岁的威利里德是一位飞机零部件技师，他说：“我们家人关系很好，我认为也是这个帮助我们度过了难关。”**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1260', 'vicissitude', '[vɪsɪsɪtud]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vicissitude', '{n.}++变化，变革，变迁**++(事物的)推移；交替，变换**++[复数](人生的)盛衰，荣枯，沉浮**++多变，易变**', '++So great a vicissitude in his life could not at once be received as real.**++他的生活中发生了如此巨大的变迁，他一时还无法相信是真的。**++If vicissitude is concealing the moral progress, then where the progresses manifests lies in?**++如果说变迁隐含着道德的进步，那么进步体现在哪里？**++First chapter elaborated education-through-labor historical vicissitude and the development tendency.**++第一章论述了劳动教养的历史变迁与发展趋势。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1261', 'immersion', '[ɪmɝʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=immersion', '{n.}++浸没，沉浸**++专心；陷入；沉溺**++【宗教】浸礼；洗礼**++【天文学】掩始[亦作 ingress,参较 emersion]**++(尤指第二语言的)集中传授**{adj.}++(学外语时)沉浸式强化训练的**', '++And so on. Immersion trains your mind to work efficiently in the ways you need it to.**++沉浸到你目标中去，能训练你的头脑，让它以你期待的方式，变得高效。**++On one particular Friday, I left the office after a week full of overtime and complete immersion in the work.**++在一个普通的星期五，在一个星期的加班和在工作中完全的沉浸之后我离开办公室。**++Jobs@s immersion in Zen and passion for design almost certainly exposed him to the concept of ma, a central pillar of traditional Japanese aesthetics.**++以乔布斯对禅的沉浸和对设计的热爱，他几乎肯定钻研过“无”这一日本传统美学的中心支柱观念。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1262', 'illusory', '[ɪlusəri]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=illusory', '{adj.}++幻觉的，错觉的；梦幻似的；迷惑人的**++虚幻的；虚假的；不实际的**', '++Secondly, if the self is an illusion, then aren’t subjective insights from meditation illusory as well?**++其次，如果自我是错觉，那么来自于冥想的主观视角不也同样是错觉？**++MacKay first observed this effect on the wallboard of a BBC studio: the broadcasting staff had been annoyed by illusory shadows running up and down blank strips between columns of parallel lines.**++麦凯是在BBC的一个录音室里第一次看到这个效果的： 那位正在播音的职员被平行线柱上线条空白间上下跳动的阴影错觉搞得很不耐烦。**++Yet many fear that the calm is illusory.**++然而，许多人担心，平静是虚幻的。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1263', 'sinuous', '[sɪnjʊəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=sinuous', '{adj.}++弯曲的；蜿蜒的**++动作柔软的**++错综复杂的，情节曲折的**++邪门歪道的，不正当的**++(叶子边缘)呈深波状的**', '++The great creator raised his sinuous, powerful, flexible arm, and we know where we stand.**++伟大的造物主抬起了他弯曲的，有力的，灵活的手臂，我们知道了我们的立场。**++Why It@s Innovative: The sinuous Pythonbrug is one of the most modern bridges in Amsterdam, a city famous for its traditional canal bridges.**++创新点：阿姆斯特丹以运河桥著称，而蜿蜒的巨蛇桥是阿姆斯特丹最具现代气息的桥梁之一。**++The narrow, uneven, sinuous streets, full of angles and turns, were admirably chosen; the neighborhood of the Halles, in particular, a network of streets more intricate than a forest.**++令人折服地选择了那些狭窄、不平整、弯曲、凸凹、转拐的街道，特别是菜市场那一带，有着象森林一样紊乱的街道网。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1264', 'befriend', '[]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=befriend', '{vt.}++对…以朋友态度相待，与…交朋友，亲近：**++帮助，照顾，扶助：**', '++We are willing to befriend the weak and the poor.**++我们愿意扶助弱者与穷人。**++In Damon Knight’s 1950 short story "To Serve Man, " aliens befriend us only to eat us.**++在达蒙爵士在1950年写的故事“服务人类”中，外星人帮助我们的目的是最后吃了我们。**++How do you measure the impact of the Peace Corps when two volunteers befriend a poor adolescent boy and he grows up to become president of Peru?**++对于两个志愿者和一个贫穷的少年结为朋友，结果他长大后成为秘鲁总统，你如何衡量和平队的影响？**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1265', 'tribute', '[trɪbjut]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=tribute', '{n.}++贡；贡品；贡金**++贡税**++进贡的义务；交纳贡税的义务**++勒索的款项**++礼物；称赞；颂辞；称颂**++【采矿】(给予矿主或土地所有者的)开矿谢礼**', '++The conquered had to render tribute to the conqueror.**++被征服者只得向征服者称臣纳贡。**++We thought that we should put some of them together as a tribute to him and the whole ISS crew.**++我们便把其中的一些照片集中在一起，并向他和空间站全体工作人员表示敬意。**++If I should happen to be a catalyst more than others, I consider that a tribute to those who have inspired me.**++如果我恰好比其他人更好地起到催化剂的作用，那么我会考虑为所有启示过我的人送上礼物。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1266', 'opaque', '[opek]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=opaque', '{adj.}++不透明的，不透光的**++(对声音、热、辐射等)不传导的**++不反光的；不发亮的；暗的；单调的**++难理解的，晦涩的**++迟钝的，愚钝的**{n.}++不透明体**++【摄影术】遮光涂料**{vt.}++使不透明**++使不传导(热等)**++使难理解**++【摄影术】使(底片)遮光**', '++You can do that, but I find the syntax kind of opaque.**++您可以这样做，但是我发现语法有些不透明。**++A second laser can then be fired through the normally opaque sodium; it passes through, but not much faster than a racehorse can run.**++然后，通过通常不透明的钠发射第二束激光；光线虽能通过, 但它运动的速度不会比一匹赛马更快。**++China not only censors much more content, but has a deliberately opaque system in which no one can be sure who is censoring what, or on what grounds.**++中国不仅审查过多的内容，而且有一个精密的不透明的系统，没有人确定谁在审查，审查什么，为什么审查。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1267', 'cylindrical', '[səlɪndrɪkl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=cylindrical', '{adj.}++呈圆筒形的**++圆柱体的[亦作 cylindric]**', '++Rollit is a cylindrical experimental house that includes everything you’d need in a home for one.**++罗利特是一个圆柱体的实验房屋，包括在居家中需要的所有东西。**++While it@s difficult to visualize a five-dimensional object in our three-dimensional space, black strings would be cylindrical, researchers said.**++研究人员说，虽然我们很难想象在三维空间里可以看到五维的物体，可是黑弦将会是圆柱形的。**++During auditing, Haggis grasped a cylindrical electrode in each hand; when he first joined Scientology, the electrodes were empty soup cans.**++听析过程中，哈吉斯每只手握一个圆柱形的电极；当他第一次加入山达基时，电极就是空的汤罐头盒。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1268', 'compaction', '[kəmpækʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=compaction', '{n.}', '++Thus, because of compaction, it will not encounter fragmentation issues that CMS might.**++这样，由于压缩的原因，它不会遇到CMS可能会遇到的碎片问题。**++If your MongoDB server crashes, you should repair the database to check for any corruption and perform some data compaction.**++如果 MongoDB 服务器崩溃，应修复数据库以检查错误并执行一些数据精简。**++Each of these systems has its trade-offs, but generally the compaction phase is an expensive one in terms of time and effort.**++每个这样的系统都有自己的平衡方法，但一般说来压缩阶段在时间和工作上都耗费颇多。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1269', 'capsize', '[kæpsaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=capsize', '{vt.}++使(船等)倾覆：**++使(船等)倾覆：**{vi.}++(船等)翻，倾覆：**++(船等)翻，倾覆：**', '++If a ketch had larger sails than an equivalent sloop, it would heel more (making sailing less efficient) and be more likely to capsize.**++如果双桅帆船拥有比同等尺寸的单位帆船更大的帆，它在航行时会倾斜得更多，使得航行效率变低，也更容易翻船。**++"Because it adheres to the surface of the water, it cannot capsize," he said, "So it can withstand quite severe weather.**++“由于它紧紧吸附于水面，翻船是不可能的。” Biderman说，“因此，它能挺过相当恶劣的天气。**++Provides no (unweighted board) or less (weighted board) ballast, compared to a fixed keel, to resist capsizing and ensure recovery from a capsize**++比起固定龙骨而言，它只能提供零压载（无负重龙骨板）或少量压载（带负重龙骨板），因此在抵抗倾覆和从倾覆中归位方面较为不利**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1270', 'porcelain', '[pɔrsələn]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=porcelain', '{n.}++瓷(料)；[总称]瓷器**++一件瓷器**++有光卡片纸**{adj.}++瓷的；瓷制的**++精美的**++脆的；易碎的**', '++These porcelain plates have rather original designs on them.**++这些瓷盘的花纹很别致。**++I don@t know enough about porcelain to be able to price these plates.**++我不太懂得瓷器，估计不出这些盘子的价钱。**++To this class of substance belong mica, porcelain, quartz, glass, wood, etc.**++属于这类物质的有云母、瓷器、石英、玻璃、木材等等。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1271', 'delineate', '[dɪlɪnɪet]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=delineate', '{vt.}++画出(或勾画出)…的轮廓，描绘出…的外廓，描出…的外形：**++描述，叙述：**++刻画，描写：**', '++First, I used comments to delineate sections of the code.**++首先，我使用了注释来描绘代码的各个部分。**++We delineate three separate mechanisms, friction, suction, and interlocking, that contribute to the gripping force.**++我们描绘出三个独立的力学机制，摩擦力，吸力，交错力，这有助于握力的提升。**++During this phase organizations delineate additional SOA capabilities, agree on policies for service reuse across lines of business, establish processes to guarantee service levels, and so forth.**++在此阶段，组织描绘出了附加的 SOA 能力，对跨业务线的服务复用的策略达成一致，建立过程以保证服务水平，等等。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1272', 'motif', '[motif]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=motif', '{n.}++[法语]**++(文艺作品的)主题， 中心思想；中心人物；中心事件；中心情景**++(衣服的)花边**++(服装设计、图案画、室内装饰的)基调，基本图案；基本色彩**++(汽车等上面的)商标饰物**++【音乐】动机，乐旨**++主格调，特色**++主旨，动机**', '++What is the motif of this year?**++知道今年教师节的主题吗？**++But the biblical account as much as it borrows from that motif again Takes pains to distinguish and elevate the human.**++但是圣经中许多叙述又一次从此借鉴主题,努力区别人类，并使他成为更高级的创造物。**++Let@s see what happens here, just the motif, one, two, three, four, three four, one two, and then the theme.**++让我们看看到底发生了什么,正是动机,一,二,三,四,一遍又一遍,然后是主题**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1273', 'intervention', '[,ɪntɚvɛnʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=intervention', '{n.}++介入；插入**++干预；干涉；妨碍**++调停 ；斡旋**++[美国英语](父母对子女进行指导的)介入教学，父母对孩子的教育(或辅导)；家庭教育**', '++So what we would do is that we would then perform an intervention.**++所以我们要做的是对他们进行一些干涉。**++This is the logic of intervention, but it is not in the remit of the UN resolution.**++这是北约进行军事干预的逻辑，但却并不在联合国安理会决议的条款之内。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1274', 'ambient', '[æmbɪənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=ambient', '{adj.}++周围的，四周的；环抱的，围绕的；各方面的**++流通的**{n.}++周围环境，氛围**', '++Currently, induction-loop systems and hearing aids can be used to improve the volume of ambient sounds, but cannot target and amplify specific sounds effectively.**++当前，感应回路系统和助听器可以用来提高周围声音的音量，但不能瞄准目标并有效地放大特定的声音。**++You@re in conversation with one person but the signal to noise ratio is low, meaning his voice, the signal, is quiet relative to the ambient conversational noise.**++你正在和一个人谈话，但是信号和噪音的比率低，也就是说，对方的声音（信号），相对于周围的谈话声（噪音）是安静的。**++The sound waves collected from a larger area resonate inside it and we hear a greater amount than usual of the ambient sound around us, though in a jumbled up form.**++从周围大范围空气中收集来的声波会在贝壳里面产生共鸣，这样我们就能听到更多环绕在我们四周的杂音，不过听起来杂乱不堪。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1275', 'erratic', '[ɪrætɪk]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=erratic', '{adj.}++无固定路线(或目标)的；游移的，周游的；漂泊的**++不规则的，不确定的，不稳定的；漂忽不定的；任意的**++(人、行为等)古怪的，偏执的，乖僻的，反复无常的**++【地质学】移动的，漂移性的**++【医学】游走的，移动的**++[古语]流浪的，游牧的**{n.}++怪人，乖僻的人，反复无常的人**++漫游者；漂泊者；流浪者**++【地质学】漂块，漂砾**', '++He would warn, as he often did, about "erratic swings" in the money supply.**++就像以前常常做的那样，他会对货币供给的“不稳定波动”发出警告。**++Her behaviour became increasingly erratic, and she was often drunk on stage.**++她的行为越来越古怪，有时在舞台上都是醉醺醺的。**++So many readers have sent messages saying that their boss is as erratic and as bonkers as yours that it makes one wonder if there are any normal, stable ones around - especially in investment banking.**++许多读者已经发来邮件说，他们的老板像你的老板一样古怪，而且精神不正常。 这使人想知道，是否还存在正常、可靠的老板——特别是在投资银行业。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1276', 'deliberation', '[dɪ,lɪbəreʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=deliberation', '{n.}++考虑，细想，深思熟虑；研究**++[常作复数](做出决定前的)磋商，商议，协商，评议，审议，协议**++审慎，慎重，从容，沉着，不慌不忙**++缓慢**', '++During this long deliberation process, the justices remain open to persuasion, and it is not unusual for a justice to change his or her mind about a case.**++在这一长时间的审议期间，大法官们始终愿意听取不同意见，而一位大法官改变其对某一案件的意见并不足为奇。**++After some deliberation, the group agreed to have structured classroom readings each day by two featured writers, along with more informal collaborations.**++经过一番考虑，大家同意除了实行非正式合作外，每天安排两位有特色的作家在课堂上朗读作品。**++The Chinese delegation will advance its view and proposition on the future work of the Council and participated in the deliberation on all questions with a positive and constructive attitude.**++中国代表团将在会上提出对理事会未来工作的看法和主张，以积极和建设性态度参与各项议题的审议。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1277', 'cottage', '[kɑtɪdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=cottage', '{n.}++小屋；村舍；小房子**++(度假用的)别墅**++(学校、医院的)单幢住宅，单幢小楼**++(同性恋者常去进行约会和性活动的)公共厕所**{vi.}++(尤指同性恋者)群聚在公共厕所：**++(尤指同性恋者)群聚在公共厕所：**', '++I saw a cottage nestling in the woods.**++我看到隐映在树林中的乡村别墅。**++Roses and honeysuckle entwine the little cottage.**++玫瑰与忍冬盘绕着小屋。**++I heard a big crack in my leg bone. I was 200 yards from the nearest road so I screamed and screamed until a lady from a cottage down the road came to help me.**++我听到自己的腿骨发出很大的爆裂声，可是那时我离最近的公路有200码，所以我只能不停呼救，直到过了一会儿，一个小屋的女士前来帮助我。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1278', 'scant', '[skænt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=scant', '{adj.}++不足的，欠缺的**++少量的，贫乏的**++差一点点的；刚刚够的，勉强够的**++缺乏…的(of)**++吝啬的；过分节俭的**{adv.}++[苏格兰和英格兰北部方言]仅仅，勉强；几乎不 =scarcely**{vt.}++减少，在…上缩减：**++在…上少给，克扣：**++限制；为(数量、规模等)确定范围：**++藐视；忽略：**', '++With no more than minimal Greek, the Chinese have little to do with the local police, and get scant help when their cash or merchandise is stolen.**++除了和极少希腊人接触外，中国人和当地警察的联系也甚少，当他们的现金或商品被偷取时，他们从警察那里得到并不足够的帮助。**++Until we see an actual announcement from Google, almost everything we can say about this OS is speculation based on scant information.**++在我们实际看到来自谷歌的公告以前，我们对这个操作系统所能说的一切都是没有多少根据的猜测。**++Surviving on the scant rain that falls on the high desert, the surrounding natural scrubland uses far less water. The scrubland, shown in the upper left corner of the image, is tan and pale blue.**++为了在降水稀少的高地沙漠存活下来，周围自然形态的灌木丛则消耗很少的水分，可以看到这些分布在图片左上部的灌木丛是黄褐色和灰蓝色的。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1279', 'remuneration', '[rɪ,mjunəreʃən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=remuneration', '{n.}++酬劳；补偿；赔偿**++报酬；酬金；补偿物；赔偿费**', '++If you think that remuneration will cause me to biased, so be it.**++如果你认为这样的报酬会使我心存偏见，也只能那样了。**++No, not only for high pay (remuneration), but also for a good working environment.**++不，不仅是为了优厚的报酬，而且是为了好的工作环境。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1280', 'promissory', '[prɑmə,sori]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=promissory', '{adj.}++允诺的；有约束力的**++订约的；约定的**++【商业】约定支付的；(保险法中)使保险契约生效之特约条款的**', '++A promissory note establishes the terms of the loan and allows action in a court of law if the provisions fall within state contract laws.**++这份保证书写明贷款条款并产生法律效力，一旦有一方违背了，就可以用合同法的有关条例解决纠纷。**++Technically, a CD is a promissory note the issuing bank delivers to you.**++专业的来讲，存款证是开证银行提供给您的期票。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1281', 'cult', '[kʌlt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=cult', '{n.}++【宗教】礼拜，膜拜，祭礼**++(对人、主义或物等的)狂热崇拜；迷信**++崇拜的对象，迷信的对象**++[总称]狂热信徒；崇拜者，迷信者**++(宗教的)派别，教派**++邪教，异教；邪教徒，异教徒**{adj.}++狂热崇拜的**', '++...**++...**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1282', 'recipient', '[rɪsɪpɪənt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=recipient', '{n.}++接受者，接受器；容器**++【语法学】间接宾语**{adj.}++接受的；能接受的；善于接受的；接受能力强的**', '++I felt glad that I was now a giver of pleasure, not merely a passive recipient.**++我很高兴，现在我是一个快乐的给予者，而不只是被动的接受者。**++If this gives you, as the recipient of the investment, heartburn is something you have to decide.**++如果是你要接受这种类型的投资，那么你就会要面对心痛的抉择了。**++And this from another recipient, in Ontario: “We are so blessed to be on your program, and I would like to thank every woman individually, if I could.**++另一位来自安大略的受益者写道：“我很幸运参加你们的计划，如果可以，我希望能分别地感谢每个捐献者。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1283', 'pylon', '[paɪlən]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=pylon', '{n.}++塔门，两旁有塔形建筑的门道**++(古埃及寺院的)塔门**++架高压电缆的铁塔**++(飞机等的)路标塔，标杆**++塔式建筑物；塔式界标；圆锥形路标**++(标梁或大道旁标志入门的)柱台；桥塔**++(机翼下挂副油箱的)外挂架，吊架**++【医学】暂用假肢**', '++It extends six legs into the seabed to stabilize itself before installation of the pylon on which each turbine sits.**++在安装每架涡轮机的支柱前，这艘安装船先将六条腿伸入海床中，以便稳定船只本身。**++The several thousand tons of steel deck and pylon were fabricated in a factory in Rotterdam, then carried across the sea by a barge labouring in the churning swell.**++数千吨的钢铁桥面和桥塔从鹿特丹的工厂生产出来，然后由驳船运载着在翻滚的海浪中缓缓穿过大洋。**++In an undated picture, a mock-up of the A-12 spy plane sits perched upside down on a testing pylon at Area 51—part of radar tests to reveal revealed how visible, or invisible, the design was to radar.**++在一张未标明日期的图片中，一架实物模型的A-12间谍飞机倒挂着停放在51区的一个测试塔上，这是为了测试该飞机的外观在雷达上可视或不可视的程度。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1284', 'breakage', '[brekɪdʒ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=breakage', '{n.}++破裂，破损，毁损，毁坏**++损耗，损失**++[常作复数]破损物**++破损量，损耗量；损坏价值**++破损部分，破损处**++破损状态**++【商业】(如在运输中)损坏赔偿费，赔偿损失费，破损费**++(船舱内装货后)留下的空间**++(赛马等中)不付给前3名赢家的彩金(角以下的)零头**', '++Except in the rare instance of breakage, condoms are extremely effective at preventing most STDs.**++除非在极少数破损的情况下，避孕套对防止大多数的STD都有奇效。**++This way, the EJB itself can be used remotely by other clients without major breakage to existing business logic.**++通过这种方式，其他的客户端可以远程地使用 EJB 本身，而不会破坏现有的业务逻辑。**++If breakage occurs, maintaining the integrity of the structure is paramount so that people on or below it are safe.**++如果发生破坏，首要的问题是保证结构的完整以确保在其上/下的人员的安全。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1285', 'perplex', '[pɚplɛks]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=perplex', '{vt.}++使困惑；使难住；使茫然；使费解：**++使复杂化；使纠缠不清；使难办：**{n.}++[古语]= perplexity**', '++But don’t perplex the issue; it isn’t so complicated.**++但不要使问题复杂化了。 它没有那么复杂。**++Putin\@s rise continues to perplex even devoted Kremlin observers.**++普京的崛起至今让克林姆林宫的观察家们感到迷惑。**++But these potentially anonymous weapons continue to perplex and confound our thinking about the future of war and terrorism.**++但是，这些潜在的不为人知的武器继续困扰着我们，并影响着我们对于未来战争和恐怖主义的看法。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1286', 'signaler', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=signaler', '{n.}', '++Zahavi@s handicap principle - This principle states that in order to be honest, a signal must be costly to the signaler.**++扎哈维的障碍原则 -这一原则的国家，为了老实说，信号必须是昂贵的信号。**++CDI provides three compact and powerful permanent magnets for use with the CD52 Bandit Non-Intrusive Pig Passage Signaler.**++CDI提供四种结构紧凑的永久磁铁。 这些磁铁配合CD52非插入式清管器通过指示器使用。**++Zahavi@s handicap principle states that an honest signal must be costly to the signaler, meaning that only fit individuals can signal honestly.**++扎哈维的障碍原则规定，一个诚实的信号必须是昂贵的信号，也就是说，只有适合个人可以信号诚实。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1287', 'victimize', '[vɪktɪmaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=victimize', '{vt.}++使作牺牲；使受害，使受苦：**++欺骗，欺诈：**++屠杀…作为牺牲(品)[英国英语亦作 victimise]**', '++We hope you@ll read what we@ve made available to help you because holding onto unforgiveness and bitterness will only victimize you further.**++我们希望读这些文章会给你们带来些帮助。 因为沉浸在不可原谅和痛苦之中只能带来更多的伤害。**++The Pennsylvania and Florida cases have led some Americans to charge that the very laws meant to protect children are now being used to victimize them.**++宾夕法尼亚和佛罗里达的案件受到一些美国人的谴责：这个法案原意是要保护孩子的，可是现在却让孩子们成为受害者。**++But in our zeal to protect children from such dangers, we must ensure that we don@t use the law, which was enacted for their benefit, to victimize them further.**++但是，在我们积极地保护儿童避免这种伤害的过程中，我们必须确保，这部原先是为他们的利益而制定的法律，没有充当进一步伤害他们的工具。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1288', 'vigorous', '[vɪɡərəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=vigorous', '{adj.}++充满力量的；强有力的**++强健的，茁壮的；健全的**++精力充沛的；朝气蓬勃的**', '++In their need, they have registered a mandate that they want direct, vigorous action.**++他们在困难中表达了自己的委托，即要求采取直接而有力的行动。**++Though nearly 50, he is exceptionally vigorous in work.**++别看他快50岁了， 工作却是雷厉风行。**++She had a vigorous opponent.**++她遇到一个劲敌。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1289', 'befit', '[bɪfɪt]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=befit', '{vt.}', '++He was offered a couple of jobs but stayed adamant about his salary demands and about a title that would befit a man of his stature.**++他有若干个职位可以选择，但是他固执地坚持其薪水要求以及一个与其地位相称的头衔。**++Scientists think the glass was fused in a meteoritic impact 30 million years ago, making it rare and luminous enough to befit a king.**++科学家认为这种玻璃是由3000万年前的陨石冲击地面融溶而成，它的珍稀和光亮足以适用于国王。**++She has the required vulnerability, coyness and delicacy that befit her character Lucky.**++她所需要的脆弱性，羞怯与细致的合意她的性格幸运。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1290', 'periodization', '[...]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=periodization', '{n.}', '++I recently read a book titled “Periodization” by Brian P. Moran. This amazing book discusses the concept of moving away from a 12 month year, to a “12 Week Year.”**++我最近阅读了Brian P.Moran的一本叫做《周期化》（Periodization）的书，通常我们认为十二个月组成一年，但这令人惊讶的书却谈论的是用十二个星期组成一年的概念！**++"Periodization helps you reach a higher level of performance," says George Dallam, a professor of exercise science at Colorado State University-Pueblo and an elite triathlon coach.**++George Dallam认为“阶段性可以帮助你达到一个更高的水平。” ，他是科罗拉多州立大学的运动科学教授，一名印第安人，同时也是一名出色的铁人三项赛教练。**++Periodization divides a training cycle of, say, 16 to 20 weeks into phases, each with a specific goal, so you don@t have to do every type of workout all the time. In fact, you shouldn@t.**++阶段性的划分训练周期就是说以16-20周为一个周期，每个周期中有特定的目标，这样你就不用每次都要练习所有的训练方式了，实际上你也不必这样。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1291', 'revitalize', '[,rivaɪtəlaɪz]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=revitalize', '{vt.}', '++By setting yourself clear goals to achieve over the next month, you will be able to revitalize your approach to learning English.**++在下个月为自己定制清晰明了的目标，你将能够重新找到英语学习的途径。**++In any case, many of your employees might need rejuvenation, especially if they were not able to revitalize themselves over these past few months.**++在任何情况下，你的雇员中很多可能需要重新恢复活力，特别是当他们在过去几个月无法获得新生的时候。**++Perhaps this would improve the fluidity of Yemen’s rural economy, and revitalize a workforce that suffers from anemia, malnutrition, and diarrhea.**++也许这将改善也门农村经济的活力，把劳动力从贫血，营养不良和腹泻的魔爪下解放出来。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1292', 'conglomerate', '[kənɡlɑːmərət]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=conglomerate', '{adj.}++由各部分组成的；混杂聚在一起的，混合的**++联合大企业的，多业公司的**++【地质学】 砾岩(性)的**++聚成球形的**{n.}++聚集物，集合体，混合体**++【地质学】砾岩**++联合大企业，多种经营大公司，务业公司[亦称作multicompany]**{vt.}++使聚成球形；使聚集**{vi.}++聚在一处，聚集：**++聚在一处，聚集：**', '++Legend Holdings is an investment conglomerate partly owned by the Chinese government.**++联想控股是由中国政府部分持有的投资企业集团。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1293', 'endow', '[ɪndaʊ]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=endow', '{vt.}++天生具有，天赋，给予，赋予(某些天资、才能、品质等)；授予(with)：**++认为…具有某种品质(或特质、特性)：**++资助，捐助，捐赠基金(或财产)给(学院、医院、慈善机构等)，向…捐钱(或物)：**++[古语]给…嫁妆；给(寡妇)产业**', '++Books, indeed,  endow us with a whole enchanted palace of thoughts, there is a wider  prospect, says Jean Paul Richter, from Parnassus than from a throne.**++事实上，书籍赋予我们一个思想魔宫。 吉恩·保尔·里希特尔曾说，从帕纳萨斯看景色，比坐在宝座上看，视野更开阔。**++Don@t fall into the trap of thinking that the rich are rich because life haphazardly bestowed wealth upon them but chose not to endow it upon the impoverished.**++不要认为富人之所以富是因为生活偶然地给了他们财富而他们并没有选择捐赠给贫穷的人这样的思考陷阱里。**++Rather than hiding this division, the EU now needs a model in which fast-lane nations act as pioneers who endow the whole project with new purpose.**++欧盟不应掩盖分歧，而是需要采用一种模式，让行驶在快车道的成员国充当先锋，为整个欧洲一体化项目赋予新的目标。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1294', 'proximity', '[prɑksɪməti]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=proximity', '{n.}', '++With batch computing, the proximity of the business logic to the data significantly impacts performance.**++使用批处理计算，业务逻辑与数据的接近程度将极大地影响性能。**++Proximity in home decor is the placing of similar objects closer together physically, and unlike objects (decor) further apart.**++在家居装饰中，接近是指把类似的对象放在一起，不同的对象（装饰）分开放置。**++Eliminate all redundant or unnecessary crossings together with any crossings that cannot be made safe due to crossing geometry or proximity of complex highway intersections.**++取消所有过剩的或不必要的道口，包括那些由于道口地形问题或接近复杂公路叉路口而不能保证安全的道口。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1295', 'oneness', '[wʌnnəs]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=oneness', '{n.}++惟一；单一**++同一性**++一体，完整**++一致，协调**++惟一性，单一性；完整性；一体性**', '++Oneness refers to the idea of an interconnected identity.**++同一性涉及到内在联系的确认。**++Instead of trying to disidentify from the ego, we need to embrace the ego while merging it with a sense of oneness.**++不要试图从 自我作出错误的识别，我们需要在把 自我 与“ 单一性 ”的观念相合并的同时，要去包容 自我 。**++You could also move beyond that and identify yourself with pure oneness or consciousness, devoid of any particular individuality.**++也可能超越那些，用纯粹的“单一性”或缺乏特殊个性的自觉意识来识别你自己。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1296', 'dispense', '[dɪspɛns]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=dispense', '{vt.}++分发(施舍物品等)，分配，给与，分给，施与：**++【医药学】(尤指在药店、药房或按处方)配(药)；配(方)；发(药)：**++【法律】执行，施行，实施(法律等)：**++应付；处置**++豁免，免除，省却(from):**++【天主教】特许；特赦；特免：**{vi.}++[古语]特赦，豁免，特免，特许**{n.}++(俱乐部或旅馆的)工作人员专用酒吧**++[废语]=dispensation**++[废语]开销，花费，消费**', '++In 1978, BI began selling systems that allowed dairy farmers to dispense feed to their cows automatically.**++从1978，BI公司开始出售可以自动分配饲料给母牛的系统给奶牛农场主。**++When you make a selection, it changes to a state where it can dispense the merchandise (let@s say a quadruple chocolate candy bar).**++在做出选择之后，它就转变到分发商品（比如说一个巧克力棒）的状态。**++What they do: Based on a doctor@s prescription or a patient@s needs, pharmacists dispense medication.**++工作内容：药剂师负责根据医师的药方或者病人的需要分配药物。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1297', 'quantifiable', '[kwɑntə,faɪəbl]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=quantifiable', '{adj.}{vt.}++确定…的数量；用数量表示；测量，计量；量化(把质的变为量的)：**++【逻辑学】(在命题中)用量词(all， some等)加以限定**++【军事】估算**', '++So the dilemma facing pregnant women is that there is a small but quantifiable risk associated with infection and an unknown but probably only very small risk associated with the vaccine.**++因此，孕妇面对两难的处境，接种有不大但可以计量的与感染有关的风险，还有未知的但也许只是非常小的与疫苗有关的风险。**++Show your boss the quantifiable results upon returning, and tell him or her that — without all the distractions, commute, etc. — you can get twice as much done.**++回来后，向老板展示可量化的结果；告诉他/她，要是没有那些分心的事、通勤等等耽搁的话，你可以做现在两倍的活。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1298', 'paradigm', '[pærədaɪm]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=paradigm', '{n.}++范例；示例；模范；规范**++【语法学】(名词、动词等的)词形变化表**++【哲学】理论框架(模式)，范式**++聚合体**', '++However, the space shuttle paradigm is only one model of space access.**++如论如何，航天飞机的范例只是太空旅行的一种模式。**++However, we have seen one other fundamental paradigm shift during the past two decades.**++然而，我们在过去二十年中已经见到另一个基本范例变动。**++The paradigm of SQL is that the user (or application) just tells the database system what to do and the system itself figures out the best way how to do it.**++SQL 的范例是，用户（或应用程序）只需告诉数据库系统要 做什么，系统自己就会得出 如何做 这件事的最佳方法。**');
insert into TOEFLWordBook values ('1299', 'syndicate', '[sɪndɪkət]', 'http://dict.youdao.com/dictvoice?audio=syndicate', '{n.}++【经济学】辛迪加，企业联合组织，财团**++(特定事业的)私人联合会；房地产合伙购买(或租赁)团**++【新闻学】报刊辛迪加；稿件辛迪加[参较 boiler plate]**++[英国英语](尤指英国大学的)理事会，评议会特别委员会**++[美国英语](操纵各种犯罪活动的)黑社会，罪犯辛迪加**{vt.}++把…组成辛迪加；把…置于辛迪加的管理之下；把(赛马)卖给辛迪加：**++(通过稿件辛迪加)使在多家报刊上同时发表**++把(一系列电视节目等)直接售给地方电视台**{vi.}++联合成辛迪加**', '++Copyright: Project Syndicate/Institute for Human Sciences, 2008.**++版权：辛迪加项目/人文科学版，2008年**++Lundgren is Frank Castle, a man out for revenge on the crime syndicate that murdered his family -- and that’s pretty much where the movie stopped following the Marvel comic book.**++朗格扮演弗兰克·卡斯特，一个决心向杀害他家人的犯罪辛迪加复仇的男人——这就是这部影片和惊奇公司原作漫画的唯一相同之处了。**++The greater part of the rest were snatched out of my reach by a syndicate which hoped to sell them at a high price, probably in America, on the occasion of the recent tercentenary.**++其余的较大一部分在我的能力所及之外被一个辛迪加攫去了，它希望借最近的三百周年纪念之际，以高价出售它们，大概在美国。**');
